@chibuikemonwu_obi-jd9mv

1 month ago
to anyone reading, i'd say with the early part, you should first learn python before learning any of the theoretical part like math (fine if you do, it's highschool math in calculus, statistics and linear algebra), after python you should learn ML before learning the maths concepts (if you don't already know it or need refreshers), the reason is to give you that early motivation, that kick you need, plus when you actually learn the math, you'll actually understand what area the maths is applicable, plus you'd actually have a skill you can demonstrate. At least this is what worked for me, then depending on your personal goals, i personally chose to learn DL next (using pytorch because it's better for research than tensorflow), then NLP, before going into generative AI and then i learnt about computer vision. Again after learning ML and the maths, the following order is based of my PERSONAL goals.
